abstract: Ms. McCullough’s novel, set against the sweeping panorama of her native Australia, became one of the most-watched mini-series of all time.
snippet: Ms. McCullough’s novel, set against the sweeping panorama of her native Australia, became one of the most-watched mini-series of all time.
lead_paragraph: Colleen McCullough, a former neurophysiological researcher at Yale who, deciding to write novels in her spare time, produced “The Thorn Birds,” a multigenerational Australian romance that became an international best seller and inspired a hugely popular television mini-series, died on Thursday on Norfolk Island in the South Pacific, where she had made her home for more than 30 years. She was 77.

abstract: A column about a buddy who dealt with the consequences of poverty and inequality sparked a conversation about empathy, or the lack thereof.
snippet: A column about a buddy who dealt with the consequences of poverty and inequality sparked a conversation about empathy, or the lack thereof.
lead_paragraph: In my last column, I wrote about a high school buddy, Kevin Green, a warm and helpful man who floundered in a tough job market, hurt his back and died at the age of 54. The column was a call for empathy for those who are struggling, but, predictably, scolds complained that Kevin’s problems were of his own making.

abstract: The Seahawks’ most glorious smack talk on media day came on the subject of footballs deflated below the league standard.
snippet: The Seahawks’ most glorious smack talk on media day came on the subject of footballs deflated below the league standard.
lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — The charm of the N.F.L. is that every once in a while, in its utterly controlled and contrived fashion, it goes so wonderfully meta that it folds in on itself.

abstract: Marshawn Lynch responded to question after question by saying, “I’m here so I won’t get fined,” drawing attention to the rule that players must be available to reporters at the Super Bowl.
snippet: Marshawn Lynch responded to question after question by saying, “I’m here so I won’t get fined,” drawing attention to the rule that players must be available to reporters at the Super Bowl.
lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — Marshawn Lynch is so polite that he told the dozens of reporters waiting for him on Tuesday at the Super Bowl’s media day that he was going to snub them before he actually went ahead and did it.

abstract: The couple were married at the Loeb Central Park Boathouse in New York.
snippet: The couple were married at the Loeb Central Park Boathouse in New York.
lead_paragraph: Julia Nazha Numair and David Michael MacDonald were married Saturday at the Loeb Central Park Boathouse in New York. Matthew McBride, who became Universal Life minister for the occasion, officiated.

abstract: As it begins a 16th season, Lincoln Center’s American Songbook series has its most adventurous offerings yet.
snippet: As it begins a 16th season, Lincoln Center’s American Songbook series has its most adventurous offerings yet.
lead_paragraph: When Lincoln Center’s American Songbook series began in 1999, it was a nostalgic program showcasing popular standards by the likes of Irving Berlin, the Gershwins and Cole Porter. While keeping one foot in the past, it has since become a progressive, increasingly multicultural program devoted to the new as much as to the old — the kind of program that can give you Richard Rodgers or rap, or even a concert sung entirely in Spanish.
